26 Sec. 2.5. “Delivery service period” means the period:
27 1. Beginning when a driver starts operating a personal
28 vehicle enroute to pick-up goods for a delivery or series of
29 deliveries as documented via a digital network controlled by a
30 delivery network company;
31 2. Continuing while the driver transports the requested
32 deliveries; and
33 3. Ending upon delivery of the requested goods to:
34 (a) The customer or the last customer in a series of
35 deliveries;
36 (b) A location designated by the customer or the last
37 location so designated in a series of deliveries; or
38 (c) A location designated by the delivery network company,
39 including, for purposes of returning the goods.
40 Sec. 2.6. “Digital network” means any online-enabled
41 technology application, service, website or system offered or
42 utilized by a delivery network company that enables the provision
